# Anote-APP

## Project Setup

### 1. Clone the Repository
Clone the repository to your computer:

```bash
git git clone --recurse-submodules https://github.com/julitw/Anote-APP.git
cd Anote-APP
```

### 2. Create a `.env` File
Create a `.env` file in the project folder with the following content:

```env
POSTGRES_USER=your_user
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=your_password
POSTGRES_DB=your_database
POSTGRES_HOST=database 
POSTGRES_PORT=5432

CLARIN_API_KEY=your_api_key
```

Do not add the `.env` file to the repository. To make sure it is ignored, run:

```bash
echo ".env" >> .gitignore
```

### 3. Run the Application with Docker
To start the application, run:

```bash
docker-compose up --build
```

To stop it, run:

```bash
docker-compose down
```

